---
title: IOC Service — Admin Manual Sync Flow
---
sequenceDiagram
    participant Admin as Admin Browser
    participant Flask as Flask App
    participant AuthCheck as Session Auth\n+ CSRF Check
    participant FeedOps as enqueue_sync_for_source\n(feed_ops.py)
    participant DB as PostgreSQL\n(sync_jobs)
    participant Worker as Background Worker
    participant Adapter as Feed Adapter
    participant ExtAPI as External Feed API

    Admin->>Flask: POST /admin/sync\n{source: "misp"}
    Flask->>AuthCheck: Validate session + CSRF token
    AuthCheck-->>Flask: 400 CSRF Fail / 403 Forbidden
    Flask->>FeedOps: enqueue_sync_for_source("misp", feed_rows, …)
    FeedOps->>DB: SELECT feed WHERE source_id=misp
    FeedOps->>DB: SELECT SyncJob WHERE status IN (queued,running)
    alt Already queued/running
        FeedOps-->>Flask: {reused: [job_id]}
    else Feed incomplete config
        FeedOps-->>Flask: {blocked: ["misp"]}
    else Ready
        FeedOps->>DB: INSERT INTO sync_jobs (status=queued)
        FeedOps-->>Flask: {queued: [job_id]}
    end
    Flask-->>Admin: 302 Redirect /admin?msg=Sync queued

    Note over Worker: Scheduler loop wakes (20s interval)
    Worker->>DB: SELECT SyncJob WHERE status=queued FOR UPDATE SKIP LOCKED
    Worker->>DB: UPDATE sync_jobs SET status=running
    Worker->>DB: INSERT INTO feed_runs (status=running)
    Worker->>Adapter: execute() with env overrides
    Adapter->>ExtAPI: HTTP GET fetch_batches()
    ExtAPI-->>Adapter: Indicators JSON
    Adapter->>DB: Upsert indicators
    Worker->>DB: UPDATE feed_runs SET status=success, fetched_count=N
    Worker->>DB: UPDATE sync_jobs SET status=success, result_json={…}
    Worker->>DB: INSERT INTO app_logs (feed_sync_completed)
